</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ufilastilapplepie.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Filastil Applepie</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Federation Admin</span><br>  Posts: 140<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/27/02 6:49:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8/25 - Fear</span><hr size=1> First i should mention it was a succesfull raid in my eyes and had a flawless break. And reign did a good job leading it.<br>
Nevertheless there are alot things that can and needed to be improved.<br>
<br>
The way it was fought it is almost impossible to control agro as a highlevel caster. The Ping Pong is a direct result of the assist. I go after mob by judging health but when melees engaged before MT did i get agro thats simple (mob at 70% before MT has chances to get real agro).<br>
On break in I only got agro after the third nuke (done two times) on fight later i got sometimes agro after first nuke. Nuking later is not really possible since mob dead using lower nukes possible but than i can stay out of raid also.<br>
<br>
Lachadan three Reasons why a wizard (caster) should never be in melee range. <br>
First alot of mobs have small melee radius it is already hard enough to pack  all the melees there additional Casters make it harder for rogues to get behind mobs and for other tanks to hit at all.<br>
Second Proximity agro when you in melee you will get agroed much more often that means you either die (slow down riad) or waste cleric mana for health result in slow down too.<br>
Third places like HoT a caster should be behind wall when he not casting to avoid the Area Effect otherwise you waste mana again and slow raid down again.<br>
<br>
<br>
This part is not special for this Raid and nobodys fault but something i have to say :<br>
<br>
One thing that was not mentioned here yet and some will prolly disagree. More than 5 groups are too many in any plane raid I have been yet (I personally would lower to 4 max)<br>
It slows down a raid heavily in several ways. First buffing takes much longer. People start to go LD with many people around, it seeems the adds need much longer to be under control (I guess much harder for chanters to notice a mob that comes from other side). I am more than conviced that we could have cleared the plane (apart from Golems) with the two break in groups faster than with all 5+ groups.<br>
Sure we need more for the Golems but we were too much what you could have seen in an totally unplaned fight against the hardest Golem and still winning.<br>
Result Plane is boring and no challenge. I havent had so much fear planes yet (3 altogether) but I already get annoyed by it apart from break in. <br>
 <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=79329">Filastil Applepie</a> <br>
Sorcerer<br>
Officer of the <a href="http://www.lolf.de">Legion of Little Folk</a> <br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ucompboy484.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CompBoy484</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Soldier of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 89<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/27/02 11:20:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.eq-darklegion.com/images/Oumphoto2.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8/25 - Fear</span><hr size=1> *Sneaks into the thread*<br>
<br>
From what I have read, it seems that 6 groups killing mobs with very little HP compared to the raid's DPS seems highly inefficient.  Wouldn't it be better to split the raid into multiple killing parties, therefore killing multiple mobs in about the same time you would kill 1?  Eg, have 2 groups per party (if we are talking 6 groups total) with a puller each (although I don't know if the pullers would end up stepping on each others toes or not.)  Then, when a bigger mob comes (named stuff I guess) go into the normal killing method.  Really what Taku suggested, I guess.  Anyways, that's my 2cp. <p><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=56791" TARGET="_blank"><IMG SRC="http://www.eq-darklegion.com/images/Oumsig4.gif"><BR><B>Oumlagar, 56 Luminary</A> of the <A HREF="http://www.eq-darklegion.com">Dark Legion</A> on Povar</B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000060><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ustoneglacier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stoneglacier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Mob Acquisition Coordinator</span><br>  Posts: 119<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/27/02 2:53:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8/25 - Fear</span><hr size=1> I agree, we had overkill.  I guess I didn't really see that, and I think you're all right, that was the main problem.<br>
<br>
However, this was the first raid for quite a few people ( I noticed a bunch of MD people said it was there first).  If I were to take just 3 groups or so, the wouldn't have been able to come.  I wanted lots of people to get the experience of a plane raid, and I really hate turning people down. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87219>Reign Cloud</a> <BR>
56 Master of the Legion of Other Folk <BR>
Stoneglacier Thanos <BR>
52 Cleric of
