"The streets will flow with the blood of the nonbelievers!!!!" <BR></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000080><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ucloudsoul.showPublicProfile?language=EN>cloudsoul</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>General of the Federation</span><br>  Posts: 323<br> <font color=#70DB93>(8/27/02 7:27:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub70.ezboard.com/ffederationofpovarfrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=83.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 8/25 - Fear</span><hr size=1> <br>
The split raid idea is something worth considering, one party clearing north and one clearing south then coming together for the golems would add a new twist.<br>
<br>
Number of groups is hard to judge, if the majority of people are low 50s and high 40s you'll need 4-5 groups like the old days, with a 55+ raid you could prolly manage with 2 groups.<br>
<br>
Its the kael syndrome we've talked about, less numbers makes it more exciting but does that then mean we stop people coming?<br>
<br>
It was only a couple of weeks ago we had a few raids with less people than we wanted, Ministrys recent expansion and the addition of the Mystics have turned that around a little and given us a lot of new soldiers for our battles.<br>
<br>
I cringe now at some of the first fear pick up raids I went on with 50-60 people in the zone but I doubt we'll get that bad its always going to be a balance of how many people we need and how many want to go but with virtually all fed raids being sign up we should be able to handle it well.<br>
